Commitment to a fund that makes investments in small and mid-sized companies to support them to grow from a local presence and increase jobs.
A commitment by CDC to the A4C S Feeder LP investment fund. The fund makes investments across Africa in consumer services, financials, education and healthcare.
A commitment by CDC to the Atlantic Coast Regional Fund. The fund makes investments primarily in west and central Africa to support small and medium sized enterprises.

A commitment by CDC to the Actis Energy 3C Sub-Feeder LP investment fund. CDC's capital will be exclusively used for investment in energy projects in Africa and South Asia. The fund will actively seek out renewable energy projects.

A commitment by CDC to the African Development Partners II investment fund. The fund will invest throughout Africa, providing much-needed risk capital to businesses to help them grow, develop and increase the contribution they make to their local economies, including providing employment.

A commitment by CDC to the APF-II India Holdings Private Limited investment fund. The fund makes investments in Indian small and medium enterprises with a focus on scaling up affordable models in the healthcare, logistics, infrastructure services and consumer goods sectors.

A commitment by CDC to the Aavishkaar Goodwell India Microfinance Development Company II Limited investment fund. The fund makes investments that support enterprises active in the microfinance sector in India in order to increase access to finance for low income families in rural areas and low-income states.

A commitment by CDC to the Convergence Partners Communications Infrastructure Fund. The fund is the only infrastructure fund that is dedicated solely to the information and communications technology (ICT) sector in Africa. The investment aims to tackle the current infrastructure deficit in Africa, accelerating the development of the digital economy and boosting job creation.

A commitment by CDC to the Cordiant Emerging Loan Fund IV investment fund. The fund  will focus on providing debt finance to projects, companies and banks across a wide range of sectors, usually in the form of senior, secured loans. It aims to fill the gap left by the withdrawal of western banks in emerging markets, which has made loans more costly and harder to come by for promising businesses in countries that are growing strongly.

A commitment by CDC to the 8 Miles investment fund. The fund focuses on investments in agribusiness, consumer and retail, health, telecoms and financial services with the aim of providing jobs, skills and growth in Africa.
